Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on Vehicular Networks and Vehicle-to-Infrastructure (V2I) systems. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes an uncertainty-aware resource allocation method for the federated environment. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is relevant as the paper proposes edge computing for resource allocation. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper discusses the development of a V2I system that provides real-time response to autonomous vehicles. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper proposes a method for dynamically allocating service requests among Base Stations.
